HEADWORD: Teneriffe
<hw>Ten`er*iffe"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A white wine
resembling Madeira in taste, but more tart, produced in Teneriffe, one
of the Canary Islands; -- called also
<altname>Vidonia</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tenerity</ent>⟦br⟧
